 These Purchase Order Terms and Conditions (“Conditions”), and the Purchase Order (with any and all appendices, and/or exhibits thereto or otherwise
issued by 1MK Retall ) (collectively, the “Purchase Order’) by and between {MK Retail and the Supplier (as defined in the Purchase Order). (1MK Retail
and Supplier, collectively, the “Parties* and each a “Party”), constitute the entire agreement between the Parties and supersede and replace any and all
prior discussions and agreements between the Parties. These Conditions shall govern and be incorporated into each contract for the purchase of goods
by 1MK Retail and may only be varied with the written agreement of 1MK Retail . No terms or conditions put forward at any time by the Supplier shall
form any part of this contract.

Acceptance and Limitations
The Purchase Order shall be deemed accepted by the Supplier on the earlier of (a) shipment of goods ordered, in total or in part; or (b) within
7 days of issuance by 1MK Retail , in the absent of written notification to 1MK Retail of non-acceptance.

Changes

4MK Retail may make changes to the Purchase order at any time and the Supplier shall accept such changes. If a change by 1MK Retail
causes an increase or decrease in the cost or time required for the Supplier's performance, as soon as practicable, the Parties shall mutually
agree to an adjustment, and the Purchase Order shall be modified accordingly. If price, terms, delivery schedule and any other expressed
condition of the Purchase Order cannot be achieved or met by the Supplier, 1MK Retall must be notified and agree in writing any variation.

Price and Invoice
1MK Retail shall pay the purchase price stated in the Purchase Order in consideration of the supply of Goods and the said prices shall not be
subject to any increases without the written consent of 1MK Retail .

The Supplier shall submit valid and proper tax invoice to 1MK Retail containing all appropriate references, in respect of each consignment
delivered under the Purchase Order. The Supplier shall further deliver 3 copies of the Supplier's delivery order with each consignment for 1MK
Retail 's acknowledgement.

Goods

Goads (“Goods”) shall be to the reasonable satisfaction of 1MK Retail and shall conform in all respects with any particulars specified in the
Purchase Order and the Supplier warrants that the Goods shall (a) conform to quantity, quality and description in the Purchase Order, (b) be
of sound material and workmanship, (c) conform in all respects with samples, patterns, specifications and drawings, and (d) fit and sufficient
for the purpose which the Goods are ordinarily used. 1MK Retail relies on the skill and judgement of the Supplier in the supply of Goods and
the performance of the Purchase Order.

Mock-up

In cases where mock-up sample is required, the Supplier must submit the mock-up sample to 1MK Retail and obtain its written instruction
before the Supplier may proceed with production, In the event that the mock-up sample submitted is not satisfactory to 1MK Retail and the
Supplier fails to rectify the same and obtain the written instruction of 1MK Retail , 1MK Retail has the unfettered right to cancel the Purchase
Order whereupon the Supplier shall, upon receipt of any cancellation notice, refund all monies paid to the Supplier, if any, and have no claims
whatsoever and howsoever against 1MK Retail , including but not limited to the cost of the mock-up sample.

Delivery and Freight Charges
All packing, shipping, unloading, assembling and installation are included in the purchase price set in the
Purchase Order and 1MK Retail shall not be charged additional amounts for such services.

The Goods shall be delivered to the place named In the Purchase Order. Any access to 1MK Retall 's premises shall be at a time determined
by 1MK Retail absolutely and any labour or equipment that may be provided by 1MK Retail in connection with delivery shall be provided
without acceptance of any liability by 1MK Retall . The Supplier shall indemnify 1MK Retail against ail claims, proceedings, actions, damages,
costs, expenses and other liability or loss in respect of any death or personal injury, or loss of or damage to property, occurring In the course
of delivery or installation or performance of services to the extent that such death or injury, or loss or damage is caused directly or indirectly by
any wrongful act or omission of the Supplier or anyone under his direct/indirect control (‘Employees”).

When any access to {MK Retail 's premises is necessary in connection with delivery or installation, the Supplier and his Employees shall
comply with all rules and regulations, fire safety and any other regulations implemented by {MK Retail in the premises. {MK Retail shall
provide copies of his written security procedures to the Supplier on request. 1MK Retail shall have the right to carry any search of Employees
or of vehicles used by the Supplier at 1MK Retall ’s premises.

Time of delivery shall be of the essence, Fallure to deliver within the time specified in the Purchase Order shall entitle 1MK Retail (at his
option) to release himself from any obligation to accept and pay for the Goods and/or to cancel all or part of the order for the Goods, in either
case without prejudice to his other rights and remedies pursuant to the Purchase Order.

Acknowledgement
The Supplier hereby acknowledges that the Supplier has visited the premises wherever and whenever necessary and has noted and satisfied
himself as to the scope of work, nature, risk and obligations to be undertaken and have accordingly accepted to provide the said Goods.

Inspection

4MK Retail shall have the right to inspect and test all Goods delivered under the Purchase Order. Neither receipt nor payment for Goods shall
constitute acceptance. {MK Retail may reject any or all items that all nonconforming, as determined by 1MK Retail absolutely. Goods

Labelling and Packaging

The Goods shall be packed and marked in a property manner and in accordance with any statutory requirements and any requirements of the

Without prejudice to any other rights or remedies of 1MK Retail pursuant to this Conditions, the Supplier shall indemnify 1MK Retail against

The Supplier shall effect and maintain with a reputable insurance company a policy or policies of insurance covering all the matters which «®

the subject of indemnities under these Conditions. The Supplier shall produce to 1MK Retail , on request, copies of the relevant policy or
policies or other evidence confirming the existence of the cover given by those policies, together with receipts or other evidence of payment of
the latest premiums due under those policies. The terms of any insurance or the amount of cover shall not relleve the Supplier of any liabilities
under this Conditions and the Purchase order. It shall be the responsibility of the Supplier to determine the amount of insurance cover that will
be adequate to enable the Supplier to satisfy any liability referred herein.

Recovery of Sums Due to {MK Retail

Whenever under the Purchase Order any sum of money is recoverable from or payable by the Supplier (Including any sum which the Supplier
is liable to pay to {MK Retail in respect of any breach of the Purchase Order and/or these Conditions). 1MK Retall may unilaterally deduct
that sum from any sum then due or which at any later time becomes due to the Supplier under the Purchase Order. Any overpayment by 1MK
Retail (o the Supplier shail be a sum of money recoverable by 1MK Retail from the Supplier.

Independent Contractor

The Supplier, in performance of its duties, shall be an independent contractor only, and not an agent, employee or partner of 1MK Retail , and
nothing herein shall be deemed to create or imply any relationship other than that of independent contractor. The Supplier shall have no
authority to incur any obligations or expenses on behalf of 1MK Retail .

Assignment

The Supplier shall not assign any part of the Purchase Order without the prior written consent of 1MK Retail being obtained. 1MK Retall may
assign all or any part of its rights and interest in the Purchase Order at its absolutue discretion. c
Suspension

AMK Retail may suspend all or part of the supply of the Goods at any time for any period of time by notice in writing to the Supplier. The
Supplier must comply with the notice and recommence supply when notified by 1MK Retail . The Supplier shall not be entitled to any
additional payment arising as a result of the suspension.

Termination

1MK Retail may, by written notice to the Supplier, terminate the Purchase Order, or any part thereof, without assigning any reason
whatsoever. Upon receipt of notice of termination, the Supplier shall immediately stop all work in connection with the Purchase Order, 1MK
Retail shall pay the Supplier for Goods manufactured and supplied in accordance with the Purchase Order up until the date of cancellation.
Upon such payment, the title to and property in the said Goods shall pass to 1MK Retail .

Termination for Breach

In the event the Supplier breaches this Conditions, any of the terms and conditions in the Purchase Order or becomes insolvent, 1MK Retail
may cancel the Purchase Order, or any part thereof and the Supplier shall be liable for all costs Incurred by 1MK Retail in purchasing similar
Goods elsewhere,

5. You must indicate Purchase Order number on all Delivery Orders, Invoices, Packages, Shipping documents and correspondences
6. You must attached a copy of this Purchase Order with the Delivery Order during delivery.
7. Delivery accepted subject to count, weight and approval.
8. For food items, please ensure all product must have HALAL JAKIM logo on the packaging or labelling on each product.
   We have a right to reject any product without HALAL JAKIM logo.
